{"jsonrpc":"2.0","id":1,"result":{"protocolVersion":"2024-11-05","capabilities":{"tools":{}},"serverInfo":{"name":"medaka","version":"0.1.0-preview"}}}
{"jsonrpc":"2.0","id":2,"result":{"tools":[{"name":"medaka_check","description":"Type-check Medaka source and return structured diagnostics â€” the same JSON `medaka check --json` emits (stable `code`, `range`, `severity`, `help`, and a machine-applicable `fix` where available). Provide exactly one of `file` or `source`.","inputSchema":{"type":"object","properties":{"file":{"type":"string","description":"Path to a .mdk file to check."},"source":{"type":"string","description":"Inline Medaka source to check (no file on disk)."}}}},{"name":"medaka_type_at","description":"Infer the type/scheme at a position â€” the LSP hover, driven statelessly. Give a `file` path plus a 0-based `line` and `col` (LSP-style); returns the `<name> : <type>` at that point, resolving imported names against the project on disk. A position off any identifier returns a clean \"no symbol\" note, not an error.","inputSchema":{"type":"object","properties":{"file":{"type":"string","description":"Path to the .mdk file to query."},"line":{"type":"integer","description":"0-based line of the position (LSP-style, first line is 0)."},"col":{"type":"integer","description":"0-based column of the position (LSP-style, first column is 0)."}},"required":["file","line","col"]}},{"name":"medaka_symbols","description":"List a file's top-level declarations (functions, data types, interfaces, impls, â€¦) with their source ranges â€” the LSP document-symbol outline, driven statelessly. Give a `file` path; parse-only (no typecheck), so it works even on a file with type errors. A file that fails to PARSE also returns an empty list â€” pair with medaka_check to tell an empty file from a broken one.","inputSchema":{"type":"object","properties":{"file":{"type":"string","description":"Path to the .mdk file to list symbols for."}},"required":["file"]}},{"name":"medaka_definition","description":"Find the declaration that defines the identifier at a position â€” the LSP go-to-definition, driven statelessly. Give a `file` path plus a 0-based `line` and `col` (LSP-style). INTRA-FILE ONLY: it scans declarations in this same file, so a use of a name defined in ANOTHER file returns an empty result rather than a wrong location. A position off any identifier also returns an empty result.","inputSchema":{"type":"object","properties":{"file":{"type":"string","description":"Path to the .mdk file to query."},"line":{"type":"integer","description":"0-based line of the position (LSP-style, first line is 0)."},"col":{"type":"integer","description":"0-based column of the position (LSP-style, first column is 0)."}},"required":["file","line","col"]}},{"name":"medaka_fmt","description":"Format Medaka source with the compiler's canonical formatter (`medaka fmt`), driven statelessly. Provide exactly one of `file` or `source`. NEVER writes to disk â€” a `file` argument is only READ, never opened for writing; apply the returned text yourself if you want it saved. Default: returns the formatted source text. Pass `check: true` to instead get a clean/dirty verdict (`{\"clean\": true|false}`) without the full text. Input that fails to PARSE returns an isError result carrying the parse diagnostic, never a crash.","inputSchema":{"type":"object","properties":{"file":{"type":"string","description":"Path to a .mdk file to format. READ ONLY â€” the file is never written; the formatted text is returned for the caller to apply."},"source":{"type":"string","description":"Inline Medaka source to format (no file on disk)."},"check":{"type":"boolean","description":"If true, report clean/dirty instead of returning the formatted text (default false)."}}}},{"name":"medaka_lint","description":"Run the compiler's style linter (`medaka lint`) over one or more files and return structured diagnostics â€” the same JSON envelope `medaka_check`/`medaka lint --json` emit (stable `range`/`severity`/`source`, with the lint RULE NAME in `code`). Give `paths` (array of file paths); optionally narrow with comma-separated `deny`/`only`/`disable` rule-name lists (mirror the CLI's --deny/--only/--disable). Report-only â€” no autofix; apply a fix yourself if you want one.","inputSchema":{"type":"object","properties":{"paths":{"type":"array","items":{"type":"string"},"description":"Paths to .mdk files to lint."},"deny":{"type":"string","description":"Comma-separated rule names to promote to error severity (mirrors --deny)."},"only":{"type":"string","description":"Comma-separated rule names to keep, dropping findings from every other rule (mirrors --only)."},"disable":{"type":"string","description":"Comma-separated rule names to suppress (mirrors --disable)."}},"required":["paths"]}}]}}
